00:14:31,464 --> 00:14:34,901
I'M DR. NANCY TANCHEL.
I'M THE C. E. O. OF THE COMPANY.

00:14:34,901 --> 00:14:37,103
WE'RE HERE TODAY TO ASK YOU

00:14:37,103 --> 00:14:41,641
FOR AN INVESTMENT OF $500,000
FOR 20% OF OUR COMPANY.
WHEW!

00:14:41,641 --> 00:14:44,877
FOR THE PAST 15 YEARS,

00:14:44,877 --> 00:14:46,479
I'VE BEEN DESIGNING PRODUCTS

00:14:46,479 --> 00:14:49,916
FOR THE CUSTOM MOTORCYCLE
INDUSTRY.

00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:55,154
I DEVELOPED THE ENTIRE
THREE‐DIMENSIONAL PROCESS

00:14:55,154 --> 00:14:58,057
THAT IS INCLUDED
AND ALL THE ARTISTRY

00:14:58,057 --> 00:15:00,359
THAT MAKES THE HELLS BELLS
A SUCCESS.

00:15:00,359 --> 00:15:02,562
ESSENTIALLY,
WHAT I REALLY DID, THOUGH,

00:15:02,562 --> 00:15:06,099
WAS I TOOK A LEGALLY MANDATED
SAFETY HELMET.

00:15:06,099 --> 00:15:09,302
I MADE IT STRONGER,
I MADE IT SAFER

00:15:09,302 --> 00:15:12,138
AND I MADE IT 10,000 TIMES
MORE APPEALING,

00:15:12,138 --> 00:15:15,475
BECAUSE OF ALL
THE THREE‐DIMENSIONAL GRAPHICS

00:15:15,475 --> 00:15:17,910
THAT ACTUALLY EVOLVED
FROM THE SHELL. OKAY?

00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:19,812
SO...

00:15:19,812 --> 00:15:21,914
THE, UM...

00:15:23,883 --> 00:15:25,852
WE, UH...

00:15:25,852 --> 00:15:29,155
ONLY MILLIONS OF PEOPLE
WATCHING. TAKE YOUR TIME.
ALL RIGHT.

00:15:30,556 --> 00:15:34,026
(chuckles) AND BASICALLY
WHAT HAPPENED IS,

00:15:34,026 --> 00:15:37,096
UH, WE... I'M SO SORRY.

00:15:37,096 --> 00:15:39,499
A NERVOUS BIKER.
I AM REALLY NERVOUS.

00:15:39,499 --> 00:15:42,468
WELL, LET'S JUST TALK ABOUT‐‐
WE OWN A UTILITY PATENT

00:15:42,468 --> 00:15:44,837
TO PLACE
THREE‐DIMENSIONAL DESIGNS

00:15:44,837 --> 00:15:48,374
ON NOT ONLY MOTORCYCLE HELMETS,
BUT ANY KIND OF SPORTING HELMET.

00:15:48,374 --> 00:15:50,309
DO YOU HAVE
ANY SALES RIGHT NOW?

00:15:50,309 --> 00:15:53,279
YES, WE DO. WE ACTUALLY ARE
ON TRACK THIS YEAR TO BRING IN

00:15:53,279 --> 00:15:57,250
$300,000 OF SALES
JUST FOR THE MOTORCYCLE HELMETS.

00:15:58,784 --> 00:16:02,421
LET ME SEE THE ONE WITH THE FACE
ON IT, THAT ONE THAT HE'S...

00:16:02,421 --> 00:16:06,425
IT'S THE ONLY HELMET OF ITS KIND
IN THE WORLD.
BRING ANOTHER ONE UP.

00:16:06,425 --> 00:16:08,427
WELL,
THE REASON THAT WE'RE HERE

00:16:08,427 --> 00:16:11,330
AND THE REASON WE'RE SEEKING
AN INVESTMENT FROM Y'ALL

00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:13,533
IS SO THAT WE CAN GET INTO
THE MASS PRODUCTION

00:16:13,533 --> 00:16:16,002
OF THESE HELMETS.
THAT TAKES A BIG INVESTMENT.

00:16:16,002 --> 00:16:18,070
DOCTOR,
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING...
(Nancy) YES, SIR.

00:16:18,070 --> 00:16:20,273
ABOUT THE DESIGN
OF THESE THINGS.

00:16:20,273 --> 00:16:21,941
TAKE ROBERT, FOR EXAMPLE.

00:16:21,941 --> 00:16:24,043
HE'S SORT OF A, UH,
A‐A DANDY WEEKEND DRIVER.

00:16:24,043 --> 00:16:27,113
IS HE GOING TO REALLY HAVE
THE MERCHANT OF DEATH

00:16:27,113 --> 00:16:29,815
ON THE FRONT OF HIS HELMET?
YES, I WOULD.

00:16:29,815 --> 00:16:33,886
WELL, YOU KNOW, THE DESIGNS
CAN BE WHATEVER PEOPLE WANT.
NANCY, LET'S GO‐‐CAN I GO
BACK TO ONE THING...

00:16:33,886 --> 00:16:36,856
ABSOLUTELY.
THAT YOU SAID AND WE KIND OF
COMPLETELY MISSED OVER?

00:16:36,856 --> 00:16:40,526
YOU OWN A PATENT.
A UTILITY PATENT.

00:16:40,526 --> 00:16:43,462
YOU'RE THE ONLY PEOPLE
THAT CAN PUT A 3‐D DESIGN

00:16:43,462 --> 00:16:46,399
ON ANY HELMET?
(Daymond) ON <i>ANY...</i>

00:16:46,399 --> 00:16:49,869
SPORTING HELMET?
(Nancy) ANY SPORTS HELMETS.

00:16:49,869 --> 00:16:51,737
SO, MARIX, IF THAT'S TRUE‐‐

00:16:51,737 --> 00:16:54,740
AND I GUESS I HAVE TO GIVE YOU
THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT‐‐

00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:57,843
I JUST THINK THAT
THAT'S AN UNBELIEVABLE ASSET.
WE'D LOVE FOR YOU
TO CHECK IT OUT.

00:16:57,843 --> 00:17:02,381
(laughs)

00:17:02,381 --> 00:17:04,750
WHAT DOES A REGULAR HELMET
SELL FOR?

00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:07,353
$175.
THIS ONE?

00:17:07,353 --> 00:17:09,288
WELL, HOW ABOUT‐‐
WHAT'S THE PROFIT?

00:17:09,288 --> 00:17:11,891
THE PROFIT MARGIN IS OVER 50%,
WELL OVER 50%.

00:17:11,891 --> 00:17:14,760
AND IF WE WERE TO MASS PRODUCE,
BRING OUR COST DOWN

00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:18,231
EVEN A LITTLE BIT MORE,
IT WOULD EVEN BE MORE FAVORABLE.
LET'S GET DOWN TO
THE NUMBERS FOR A SECOND.

00:17:18,231 --> 00:17:21,133
2009 SALES‐‐END OF THIS YEAR,
WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'LL MAKE

00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:23,135
IN REVENUE OFF THESE HELMETS
THIS YEAR?

00:17:23,135 --> 00:17:24,270
UM... (makes whooshing noises)

00:17:24,270 --> 00:17:28,641
IT'LL BE AROUND $175,000
MAYBE A LITTLE MORE THAN THAT.

00:17:33,779 --> 00:17:36,449
GUYS, I THINK THE POTENTIAL
HERE IS TREMENDOUS,

00:17:36,449 --> 00:17:38,718
BUT IT'S TOUGH FOR ME
TO WRITE A CHECK

00:17:38,718 --> 00:17:40,720
FOR HALF A MILLION
ON THE POTENTIAL.

00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:42,421
SO I'M GONNA BOW OUT NOW.
THANK YOU.

00:17:42,421 --> 00:17:44,457
OKAY. THANK YOU.

00:17:44,457 --> 00:17:48,261
I'M IN THE SAME BOAT.
IT'S TOO LARGE A STRETCH‐‐

00:17:48,261 --> 00:17:51,297
THE OPTIMISM, THE EXCITEMENT,
I LIKE THE HELMET, I PUT IT ON‐‐

00:17:51,297 --> 00:17:54,100
I WAKE UP TOMORROW MORNING
AND I SAY TO MYSELF,

00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:56,669
"WHY DID I GIVE
THOSE GUYS $500,000

00:17:56,669 --> 00:17:58,971
JUST BECAUSE
THEY WERE SMILING AT ME?"

00:17:58,971 --> 00:18:03,776
I NEED A LOT MORE EVIDENCE
THAT THIS TRAJECTORY IS VALID,

00:18:03,776 --> 00:18:06,012
SO FOR THAT REASON, I'M OUT.

00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:11,651
THIS ISN'T MY CUP OF TEA,
SO I JUST WANNA... I'M OUT.

00:18:13,819 --> 00:18:16,656
THERE'S REALLY NO QUESTION.
THIS IS GONNA BE A HUGE PRODUCT,

00:18:16,656 --> 00:18:19,325
WHETHER WE LICENSE IT OUT OR...
THE ONLY QUESTION IS...

00:18:19,325 --> 00:18:21,694
YES?
THE NUMBER YOU PUT ON IT,
DOCTOR.

00:18:21,694 --> 00:18:24,297
I UNDERSTAND. I UNDERSTAND.
BUT, UM, YOU KNOW, AGAIN,

00:18:24,297 --> 00:18:26,232
AS YOU GUYS
HAVE ALREADY MENTIONED,

00:18:26,232 --> 00:18:28,067
THERE IS THIS PATENT INVOLVED,

00:18:28,067 --> 00:18:31,003
AND THIS PATENT
IS EXCEPTIONALLY BROAD.

00:18:31,003 --> 00:18:34,807
THERE'S A HUGE VALUE
TO THIS PATENT.
YOU'RE VALUATING THE COMPANY
AT $2.5 MILLION,

00:18:34,807 --> 00:18:37,710
AND YOU ONLY HAVE $300,000
IN SALES.

00:18:37,710 --> 00:18:41,047
TO GIVE YOU $500,000 IN CASH,
I WOULD BE CRAZY RIGHT NOW.

00:18:41,047 --> 00:18:43,983
♪♪

00:18:51,057 --> 00:18:52,792
<i>THREE SHARKS ARE OUT.</i>

00:18:52,792 --> 00:18:58,064
<i>DAYMOND OR ROBERT ARE THEIR</i>
<i>ONLY CHANCE TO MAKE A DEAL.</i>

00:18:58,064 --> 00:19:01,600
NANCY, DO YOU WANT
TO SELL A LOT OF HELMETS

00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,669
OR DO YOU WANT
TO MANUFACTURE THEM?

00:19:03,669 --> 00:19:05,938
WELL, WE WANT TO DOMINATE
THAT INDUSTRY.

00:19:05,938 --> 00:19:08,307
BUT IF WE COULD STRUCTURE
A DEAL...
MM‐HMM.

00:19:08,307 --> 00:19:10,710
WHERE WE LICENSE IT
TO SOMEBODY ELSE,

00:19:10,710 --> 00:19:13,646
WE NEVER HAVE
TO MAKE A SINGLE ONE...
RIGHT.

00:19:13,646 --> 00:19:16,182
AND YOU COLLECT
A PERCENTAGE OF A ROYALTY

00:19:16,182 --> 00:19:18,184
OR WHATEVER THE CASE IS...

00:19:18,184 --> 00:19:20,820
SURE.
ARE YOU MORE INTERESTED
IN DOING THAT

00:19:20,820 --> 00:19:25,257
OR ARE YOU MORE INTERESTED...
WELL, WE WOULD LOVE TO DO THAT.
WE WANT YOUR EXPERTISE.

00:19:29,328 --> 00:19:31,831
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT I‐‐
I'LL DO‐‐I'LL DO FOR YOU.

00:19:31,831 --> 00:19:33,699
YES?

00:19:33,699 --> 00:19:37,303
NORMALLY I WOULD ASK
FOR 51% OR 70%

00:19:37,303 --> 00:19:39,305
TO TAKE ON ALL THIS,

00:19:39,305 --> 00:19:42,508
BUT WHAT I'LL DO FOR YOU IS,
I'LL GO 50/50 WITH YOU.

00:19:44,643 --> 00:19:47,546
FOR 50% OF THE COMPANY,
I WILL GIVE YOU THE $500,000,

00:19:47,546 --> 00:19:50,149
AND MY OBJECTIVE
AT THE END OF THE DAY

00:19:50,149 --> 00:19:53,185
IS TO LICENSE THIS
TO A BUNCH OF COMPANIES.

00:19:53,185 --> 00:19:55,154
CAN I ASK THIS‐‐

00:19:55,154 --> 00:19:57,556
WILL IT‐‐WILL IT HAVE
THE SAME DETAIL

00:19:57,556 --> 00:20:00,126
AND THE‐‐THE ARTISTIC
PROPERTIES?

00:20:00,126 --> 00:20:03,262
WE WILL BE PARTNERS, AND WE WILL
MAKE THIS DECISION TOGETHER.

00:20:03,262 --> 00:20:06,599
AND ALL THE ASPECTS THAT MAKE
THIS GREAT WILL NEED TO BE THERE

00:20:06,599 --> 00:20:10,202
OR IT'S NOT WORTH IT FOR ME.
MARIX, JUST SO YOU KNOW
WHERE I STAND...

00:20:10,202 --> 00:20:13,205
I'M GONNA BE OUT. HIS
OFFER IS BETTER THAN MINE.

00:20:13,205 --> 00:20:16,609
I WAS GONNA OFFER YOU
$500,000 FOR 75%,

00:20:16,609 --> 00:20:19,945
BUT HIS OFFER IS BETTER
AS A STARTING POINT.

00:20:19,945 --> 00:20:21,881
THANK YOU.

00:20:21,881 --> 00:20:25,384
SO, GUYS, WHAT DO YOU SAY?

00:20:29,255 --> 00:20:31,624
WE'RE EXCITED TO GET
INTO BUSINESS WITH YOU.

00:20:31,624 --> 00:20:34,593
WE THINK WE CAN WORK TOGETHER

00:20:34,593 --> 00:20:37,163
AND BUILD
A BILLION‐DOLLAR BRAND.
WELL, IS THAT A YES?

00:20:39,231 --> 00:20:41,167
YES.
YOU BETCHA.

00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:43,502
IT'S A YES ON MY SIDE.
ALL RIGHT.
THANK YOU.

00:20:43,502 --> 00:20:46,238
THANK YOU.
WE'RE EXCITED. BYE.

00:20:46,238 --> 00:20:48,274
(Marix) THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
BYE.

00:20:48,274 --> 00:20:51,544
WE'VE MADE A GOOD DEAL. I THINK
DAYMOND IS THE RIGHT PERSON.

00:20:51,544 --> 00:20:53,746
HE'S INVOLVED WITH
A GOOD HISTORY OF BRANDING

00:20:53,746 --> 00:20:56,749
AND‐‐AND SALES, SO I THINK
HE'S GONNA WORK WITH US,

00:20:56,749 --> 00:20:59,218
AND WE WILL‐‐WE'RE GONNA BUILD
A BILLION‐DOLLAR BRAND TOGETHER.

00:20:59,218 --> 00:21:01,086
I MAY REGRET THAT ONE.

00:21:01,086 --> 00:21:03,155
THAT WAS PRETTY COOL, DAYMOND.
I GOTTA ADMIT.

00:21:03,155 --> 00:21:05,658
IT WAS SUCH A BIG ASK
WITH SO LITTLE REVENUE.

00:21:05,658 --> 00:21:08,561
I'M SO MAD AT YOU,
I'M GONNA RIDE AWAY.

00:21:08,561 --> 00:21:12,465
WHAT DO YOU THINK, BARBARA?
YOU LOOK ADORABLE,
BUT HE LOOKS RIDICULOUS.

